<subSubSection id="5DD16542FFC64F47FF74FBC21E7FFAD9" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="157436C9FFC64F47FF74FBC2182DFB2F" blockId="23.[140,1108,167,1355]" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="27BFEADBFFC64F47FF74FBC21D66FBE5" bold="true" box="[185,320,1117,1143]" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="27BFEADBFFC64F47FF74FBC21D1DFBE5" box="[185,315,1117,1143]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" reason="1">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named in honor of Sonia Maria Sotomayor, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the 
<collectingCountry id="6DDC7659FFC64F47FE5CFB1F1E0BFB08" box="[401,557,1152,1178]" name="United States of America" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">United States</collectingCountry>
, whose personal story and academic and professional achievements are an inspiration for people in 
<collectingCountry id="6DDC7659FFC64F47FD15FB3B1F78FB2F" box="[728,862,1187,1214]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and elsewhere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="157436C9FFC64F47FF74FB581E7FFAD9" blockId="23.[140,1108,167,1355]" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="27BFEADBFFC64F47FF74FB581D5DFB72" bold="true" box="[185,379,1222,1249]" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="27BFEADBFFC64F47FF74FB581D33FB73" box="[185,277,1223,1249]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" reason="1">Natural</emphasis>
history.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D2CB4D4AFFC64F47FE4AFB581E81FB72" authorityName="Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[391,679,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apotomoderes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sotomayorae">
<emphasis id="27BFEADBFFC64F47FE4AFB581E81FB72" box="[391,679,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">Apotomoderes sotomayorae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Mona Island, 
<collectingCountry id="6DDC7659FFC64F47FBC5FB581CE6FA96" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="23" pageNumber="56">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(Fig. 18), where it is likely widespread, though not particularly abundant, in the plateau and depression forests (
<bibRefCitation id="715A4B38FFC64F47FE25FA921F28FAB5" author="Cintron B &amp; Rogers L" box="[488,782,1293,1320]" pageId="23" pageNumber="56" pagination="10 - 64" refId="ref19117" refString="Cintron B, Rogers L (1991) Plant communities of Mona Island. Acta Cientifica, Puerto Rico 5: 10 - 64. Dejean PFMA (1834) Catalogue de la Collection de Coleopteres de M. le Comte Dejean, Ed. 2. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, Part 3: 177 - 256." type="journal article" year="1991">Cintrón and Rogers 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Most specimens were taken at night, on a variety of shrubs and trees.
</paragraph>
